title: For Sale:  WW2 Canadian Longbranch No 4 Mk1 "British Enfield" 303 dated 1944
postcontent: WW2 Canadian Longbranch No 4 Mk1 "British Enfield" 303 dated 1944. Rifle was manufactured under license in Canada by the Longbranch Arsenal for Enfield. Everything on this rifle is original except I suspect the upper front stock may be a replacement due to the slight difference in patina. All the serial numbers match including the number on the bottom of the magazine, this is rare due to soldiers swapping mags for a fresh one in the field under fire. Also the Cartouche's under the stock are still visible and all the stamps show this to be a good original rifle including the stamp to say it was accepted in England. The stock has some dings but is in good condition with no cracks. Rifling is very good, clean bright bore. Bolt action is very good and safety is fully functioning. I have put about 30 rounds thru this rifle and it is a pleasure to shoot. Comes with 27 rounds of non corrosive ammo. $450 or will trade for a WW1/WW2 Lee Enfield Mk 3 or earlier.
